
[1]oppressive

   OPPRESS'IVE, a.

   1. Unreasonably burdensome; unjustly severe; as oppressive taxes;
   oppressive exactions of service.

   2. Tyrannical; as an oppressive government.

   3. Heavy; overpowering; overwhelming; as oppressive grief or woe.
